Defendant Jamar Donte Franklin in court with attorney Jeffrey William Jensen.  Defendant Jamar Donte Franklin in custody.  Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to court by parties.
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 254 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.(Filed in 15CF1076)
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant remanded.

Defendant Jamar Donte Franklin in court with attorney Jeffrey William Jensen.  Defendant Jamar Donte Franklin in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The state is prepared to proceed to trial on count 1 only. The state moves to dismiss counts 2,3,4,5 which is granted by the court.
Jury panel in court.  Voir dire proceeded at the hour of  11:15am.  
TWELVE (12) good and lawful citizens of the County of Milwaukee, WI qualified to serve as jurors in the above entitled cause were duly impanelled.  The court releases jurors for lunch and directs them to return at 1:20pm. Court admonishes panel not to conduct any independent investigation.
CASE RECALLED.  COURT REPORTER Lori Zahn 
All parties are present in court.  Defense informs the court that there is a possibility that jurors may have seen the defendant in handcuffs at the conclusion of the morning session.  Court will ask jurors prior to panel being sworn if any of them saw the defendant in custody.
Jury in the box at 1:50pm and is questioned by the court if any of them observed the defendant during the lunch recess.  All jurors responded they did not.  Jury panel is sworn.
Court instructed jury.  Opening statements by state; defense reserves right.  Trial proceeded.  Sworn for the state:  PO Jay Ehlers; Emily Dames, DNA Analyst, State Crime Lab. Jury out of the box.  Sidebars are placed on the record.  The defense is objecting to that state calling another expert witness (DNA) which is not on the state's witness list.  The court will disallow witness.   Jury in the box, sworn for the state:  PO Dorian Andress.  State rests subject to rebuttal.  Jury out of the box.  Exhibits  1-11 received.  Defense motion to dismiss is denied by the court.  Court conducts colloquy with defendant as to his choice NOT to testify and finds it to be free and voluntary.
Jury instructions that will be presented to jury are placed on the record and agreed to by counsels.  Jury in the box.  Stipulations read to jury.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Testimony closed.  The court instructs the jury.
Closing arguments by state and defense.  Rebuttal argument by the state.  Jury retired at the hour of 4:10pm to deliberate in the charge of Sheriff's Deputies Hoffman and Spottek who were duly sworn for that purpose.  At the hour of 4:45pm the jury returned and, by their foreperson, brought in a verdict of GUILTY which was then read.  Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdict received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdict and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdict.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction.  Case adjourned to 11-17-2015 at 8:15 for sentencing.  Defendant remanded.   Defendant advised as a convicted felon he cannot carry or possess firearms or body armor and his civil rights are suspended until restored.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 17, 2015 at 08:15 am.
